Learn to code: Set-up

Dear learner,

Thanks for taking the time to install R and Rstudio ahead of the first seminar. Installation is super easy and should take < 10 mins. I haven’t tried to cover any troubleshooting here (there are too many possibilities)… so if you run into any issues, please email me for help!

If you already have R installed, you should update if you are on version 3.9 or older. There are so many awesome new features in v4.0 and up. BUT, be forewarned: a new install of R will wipe out all your existing R libraries and you’ll need to install them again (no big deal, just takes a while to download them all again). Keeping Rstudio updated is always a good idea and won’t affect your R environment!

Best wishes,

- Jason Moggridge (ja.moggridge@gmail.com)

Install R

  • Go to: https://cran.utstat.utoronto.ca/
  • See the ‘Download R for..’ links in the top section?
  • Click the version for your system (Win, Mac, Linux).
    • Win page -> click ‘base’ version, download on next page.
    • Mac page -> find the version for your processor (intel or arm) on the next page, download.
  • Once the installer package finishes downloading, open it.
  • Click ‘continue’ a bunch of times.
  • Install will complete eventually ✅
  • You can close and delete the installer package now.

Install Rstudio IDE

  • Go to: https://www.rstudio.com/products/rstudio/download/ and scroll down half a page
  • Find “RStudio Desktop - open source license - Free” -> click Download.
  • Next page will show you the version for your OS, click download.
  • Once the installer package finishes downloading, open it.
  • Click ‘continue’ a bunch of times.
  • Install should complete eventually ✅.
  • You can close and delete the installer package now.

Verify installation

You should be able to find and open the Rstudio application now. Do so and find the ‘Console’ window in the app. Type R.version in the command prompt (after the > symbol) and you should see it return the details like this (with different info for your computer):

Install tidyverse

Tidyverse is an awesome collection of packages that we will use constantly. Install it in R by typing this command into the console:

install.packages('tidyverse')

Congrats, you’re ready to go! 🎉
